      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781965102954,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Strategy Pattern",
      "fontSize": 21.149960700865186,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Strategy Pattern",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
    {
      "id": "pY1QlwDc-XT7gjSCnV5-K",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 45.022896987214835,
      "y": 4401.757643860571,
      "width": 930.8015782068045,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#f8f1ee",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 70,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1e",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1642332878,
      "version": 868,
      "versionNonce": 1269798094,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1781965991514,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Main difference b/w Visitor & Strategy is the Intent.\n\nIn Strategy-pattern we only have fixed set of Methods(); just multiple combinations of it\ncould exist in implmentations.\n- like in above Robot example, we had walk(), fly(), talk()\n- multiple permutations could be made for this like: walk+fly, walk+talk, fly, etc\n\nWhereas in Visitor we don't have fixed set of Methods(); rather they're expanding.\n- like if in Robot, we want to add new swim() Method, then it's not possible there with\nStrategy\n- but with Visitor, we can do this by having new SwimVisitor class and methods defined for\neach Robot Type",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Main difference b/w Visitor & Strategy is the Intent.\n\nIn Strategy-pattern we only have fixed set of Methods(); just multiple combinations of it could exist in implmentations.\n- like in above Robot example, we had walk(), fly(), talk()\n- multiple permutations could be made for this like: walk+fly, walk+talk, fly, etc\n\nWhereas in Visitor we don't have fixed set of Methods(); rather they're expanding.\n- like if in Robot, we want to add new swim() Method, then it's not possible there with Strategy\n- but with Visitor, we can do this by having new SwimVisitor class and methods defined for each Robot Type",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
